How to recover lost file

Under my home directory, and also under my workspace, there is a .snopshot
which keeps hourly and nightly backup.

Say if I want to recover local file from a view that I accidently cleaned
or deleted, I would go to /ws/ytse-sjc/.snapshot/nightly.0/<view_name>.

The local files are actually coded under .s.
You can find the file using:

find . | grep <filename>

